that? Well, there is a whole hierarchy of 
international associations. I think it's ICSU,

07:49.635 --> 08:02.415
International Council of Scientific Unions, and 
under that umbrella you have international

07:49.635 --> 08:02.415
associations of virtually every discipline, one 
of which is YABO. And this is a relatively recent

08:04.037 --> 08:12.430
effort to coordinate and improve communications 
between people within any one discipline

08:12.697 --> 08:24.733
directly rather than having them go through some 
common

08:12.697 --> 08:24.733
larger framework. Did this evolve out of your 
international experience, international

08:24.753 --> 08:28.238
cooperation? Well, the organization itself 
evolved quite independently of me. I had nothing

08:31.622 --> 08:42.096
to do with that, but presumably my position with it 
now is a direct result of my earlier involvement

08:31.622 --> 08:42.096
with international

08:45.856 --> 08:51.983
Okay,

08:45.856 --> 08:51.983
what is your present position? Right now, I'm the 
chairman of the U.S. group of YABO, and if things at

08:52.404 --> 09:13.129
the Edinburgh meetings progress the way I assume 
they will, I will wind up being secretary for YABO

08:52.404 --> 09:13.129
on a whole international base.

09:13.953 --> 09:16.277
Obviously, you favor international 
cooperation. Oh, very definitely. Do you think

09:18.179 --> 09:32.741
that the new legislation and negotiations being 
worked on in terms of treaties and the

09:18.179 --> 09:32.741
underdeveloped countries claiming 200 and 
possibly other model limits will interfere with

09:18.179 --> 09:32.741
international cooperation? Certainly it will, 
but the treaties are strictly political. They're

09:39.812 --> 09:41.074
not scientific at all. And we'll just take, as we 
always do, whatever's left. Okay, and what will be

09:46.941 --> 09:50.526
the organization's opinion? YOLO? Yeah. Will 
they try to negotiate? I doubt that they'll have

09:53.630 --> 09:57.315
any say in the matter. In other words, you're

09:57.335 --> 10:06.066
inclined to think then the agreements will be 
politically arrived at without any scientific

09:57.335 --> 10:06.066
input into it? with very little scientific input. 
And if it's a question of a political decision

10:10.457 --> 10:16.684
versus a scientific decision, it will always go 
political. What effect do you think this will have

10:17.765 --> 10:20.969
on oceanography? Will, for example, physical 
oceanography be limited by these decisions?

10:28.817 --> 10:31.540
Physical and geological. Because the only real 
base for the whole treaty is to provide access to

